{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Acquires "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(such as most ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"-based I\/O) which are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"started in this thread to run under "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changes the context returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not the one returned by [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], so it does not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"affect the context used by functions like [func"},{"code":"GLib.idle_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef\/pushThreadDefault()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Normally you would call this function shortly after creating a new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"thread, passing it a [struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference"},{"text":"] which will be run by a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","type":"reference"},{"text":"] in that thread, to set a new default context for all","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"async operations in that thread. In this case you may not need to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"ever call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"text":"], assuming you want","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the new [struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] to be the default for the whole lifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the thread."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t have control over how the new thread was created (e.g.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the new thread isn’t newly created, or if the thread life"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cycle is managed by a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"), it is always suggested to wrap"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the logic that needs to use the new [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] inside a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] pair, otherwise threads that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are re-used will end up never explicitly releasing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] reference they hold.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In some cases you may want to schedule a single operation in a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-default context, or temporarily use a non-default context in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the main thread. In that case, you can wrap the call to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"asynchronous operation inside a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] \/"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"] pair, but it is up to you to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ensure that no other asynchronous operations accidentally get","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"started while the non-default context is active."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Beware that libraries that predate this function may not correctly"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"handle being used from a thread with a thread-default context. For example,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_supports_thread_contexts()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLib","roleHeading":"Instance M